  "texts": [
    "First, we seek to understand how low the NP scale can be under the additional dynamical hypothesis of NP coupling dominantly to third-generation fermions.",
    "It is important to emphasize that the U(2) 5 flavor symmetry, by itself, does not dictate whether NP couples mainly to light or heavy fermions.",
    "Instead, it only provides a consistent way to differentiate these two sectors in the UV.",
    "Dominant NP couplings to the third generation can be achieved by imposing additional conditions on the parametric size of the WCs at the high scale.",
    "Our goal is to determine these conditions trying to be as general as possible, examining the bounds on all 124 CP-even independent U(2) 5 -invariant operators present in the SMEFT at d = 6 [18]."
  ],
